SIMPLE: proliferous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Proliferous
<hw>Pro*lif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>proles</ets> offspring + <ets>-ferous</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bearing offspring; -- applied to a
flower from within which another is produced, or to a branch or frond
from which another rises, or to a plant which is reproduced by buds or
gemm⟦ae⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Producing young by
budding.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Producing sexual zooids by budding; --
said of the blastostyle of a hydroid.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>Producing
a cluster of branchlets from a larger branch; -- said of
corals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Proliferous cyst</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a cyst
that produces highly-organized or even vascular structures.</cd>
<rj><au>Paget.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pro*lif"er*ous*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prolific</ent>⟦br⟧
